description:
&lt;p&gt;We welcome you to Join the Peterborough Adult Locality Team, an enthusiastic, client-focused, Secondary Mental Health Team, offering treatment for affective disorders and psychosis to the populations of the city of Peterborough and surrounding rural areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based at The Gloucester Centre you would be a part of an established, well-integrated team including consultant psychiatrists, CPN’s, social workers and Occupational therapists, psychologists and peer support worker’s, with links to other specialist services within CPFT and a very interesting and developing 3rd sector in the local area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a Band 6 Occupational Therapist to join us on a fixed term contract. This is a unique opportunity to deliver specialist Occupational Therapy interventions alongside effective care coordination with Adults experiencing mental health challenges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Currently the team is exploring how Occupational Therapy based group work could be developed to enhance the team interventions and the Recovery journey for clients. Your contribution would be welcomed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications from developing Band 5 Occupational Therapist candidates will be considered, so please do not hesitate to call and discuss the opportunity with Helen Robinson (Lead Occupational Therapist) on 07762401459, if you have any questions or wish to find out more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Helen Robinson - Lead Therapist for North Adult Locality Teams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Helen.robinson@cpft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07762 401459&lt;/p&gt;
